---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About — claure.org"
  description="Who I am, what I build, and why I run my own infrastructure."
>
  <main>
    <section style="padding: 4rem 0 2rem;">
      <div class="container">
        <div style="max-width: 700px;">
          <h1 style="font-size: 2.5rem; margin: 0 0 2rem;">About</h1>

          <div class="prose">
            <p>
              I'm Adam. I build software, run a homelab, and use AI tools to do both faster
              than should be reasonable for one person.
            </p>

            <p>
              The homelab started as a way to stop paying for services I didn't control.
              It turned into three Proxmox VMs running 17+ containers, an autonomous ops
              bot, and a local AI video pipeline. The whole thing is managed by two AI agents
              and me occasionally pressing enter.
            </p>

            <h2>The setup</h2>

            <p>
              <strong>FrontBot</strong> is the always-on operator — a Python service on a dedicated VM
              that monitors infrastructure, triages email across 10 accounts, and sends me a
              morning brief every day. It runs <code>claude -p</code> for synthesis and talks
              to me over Matrix.
            </p>

            <p>
              <strong>Desk</strong> is the development agent — Claude Code sessions where I do
              actual building. FrontBot reviews what Desk builds, proposes what's next, and
              maintains continuity between sessions.
            </p>

            <p>
              <strong>Content Forge</strong> is the latest project — an AI video pipeline that
              generates YouTube Shorts on local GPU. Voice cloning, image generation, depth-based
              parallax effects, automated subtitles. The whole thing runs on an RTX 3080.
            </p>

            <h2>This site</h2>

            <p>
              Built with <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a>, hosted on my own
              infrastructure behind Nginx Proxy Manager. I write here about the things I
              learn building and running all of this.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
